      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine and a desirable 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission. This driver-focused example boasts a linear power delivery via six individual throttle bodies and remains planted thanks to a factory-spec limited-slip M differential. The vehicle has undergone essential preventative maintenance, including a comprehensive VANOS system refresh and a recent valve clearance adjustment. The chassis is structurally sound with a reinforced rear subframe and upgraded polyurethane bushings for enhanced torsional rigidity. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the mechanical vitals\u2014including the cooling system and dual-VANOS timing\u2014are in excellent operational order. Ideal for the purist seeking a sharp, communicative chassis and a legendary powertrain.",
